!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

everywhere /ˈɛvrɪˌwɛə/

CET4 TEM4 

1. ADV You use everywhere to refer to a whole area or to all the places in a particular area. (某区域内的) 所有地方; 各地 

例： Working people everywhere object to paying taxes. 各地劳动人民都反对纳税。 

例： We went everywhere together. 我们到哪里都一起去。 

2. ADV You use everywhere to refer to all the places that someone goes to. 所到之处 

例： Mary Jo is still accustomed to travelling everywhere in style. 玛丽·乔仍然习惯于很有气派地到处旅行。 

3. ADV You use everywhere to emphasize that you are talking about a large number of places, or all possible places. 到处 (强调地方之多或所有可能的地方) [强调] 

例： I saw her picture everywhere. 我到处看到她的照片。 

4. ADV If you say that someone or something is everywhere , you mean that they are present in a place in very large numbers. 遍地 (强调在某地数量之多); 到处 

例： There were cartons of cigarettes everywhere. 到处都是香烟盒。

